  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several international efforts to combat money laundering:\n\n1. Financial Action Task Force (FATF)\n- An international organization that sets global standards\n- Develops recommendations for preventing money laundering\n- Identifies high-risk jurisdictions\n\n2. United Nations Conventions\n- UN Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- UN Convention against Corruption\n- Provide frameworks for international cooperation\n\n3. International Monetary Fund (IMF) guidelines\n- Provides recommendations and assists countries in developing anti-money laundering policies\n\n4. Basel Committee on Banking Supervision\n- Sets international banking standards\n- Provides guidance on preventing financial crimes\n\n5. Individual Country Laws\n- Most developed countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws\n- Requirements for financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n\n6. Egmont Group\n- International network of financial intelligence units\n- Facilitates information sharing between countries\n\nThese international frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across borders by promoting cooperation and setting common standards.",
